comments.name: PR54V
comments.text: I54V is a non-polymorphic PI-selected mutation that contributes reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except DRV.

comments.name: PR82A
comments.text: V82A is a non-polymorphic mutation selected primarily by IDV and LPV. It reduces susceptibility to these PIs and contributes cross-resistance to each of the remaining PIs except DRV and TPV.

comments.name: PR90M
comments.text: L90M is a non-polymorphic PI-selected mutation that reduces susceptibility to each of the PIs except TPV and DRV.

comments.name: PR10IV
comments.text: L10I/V are polymorphic, PI-selected accessory mutations that increase the replication of viruses with other PI-resistance mutations.

comments.name: PR20R
comments.text: K20R is a highly polymorphic PI-selected accessory mutation.

comments.name: RT70R
comments.text: K70R causes intermediate resistance to AZT and possibly low-level resistance to D4T, DDI, ABC and TDF.

comments.name: RT215F
comments.text: T215F is a TAM that causes intermediate/high-level resistance to AZT and d4T, low-level resistance to ddI, and potentially low-level resistance to ABC and TDF.

comments.name: RT219QE
comments.text: K219Q/E are accessory TAMS associated with reduced susceptibility to AZT and possibly d4T.

comments.name: RT101Q
comments.text: K101Q is a relatively non-polymorphic mutation that is weakly selected in patients receiving NVP and EFV. It is of uncertain phenotypic and clinical significance.
